description: Application for the approval of Reserved Matters pursuant to planning permission PP/2015/4682 dated 18/02/2016, condition 2 pertaining to the first phase of development ("Phase A")
decision_conditions: To include:
'Use Class' - uses referred to in this permission to relate to the Use Classes Order 2005

'Part' - this could relate to a building block, a section of public realm, an area of open space etc and will be agreed with the London Borough of Ealing as the local planning authority for each Reserved Matters application, to ensure that all reserved matters are approved for a particular element of the scheme before that element is implemented
'Phase' - means a phase as approved pursuant to the Construction Phasing Programme
'Commencement of Development' unless otherwise stated, this will exclude demolition; site
'Preparation Works, site remediation works, archaeological investigations, formation of accesses and utility works but shall otherwise include works to implement this permission.

'In consultation with Transport for London (TfL), - means where any approval from the London Borough of Ealing as local planning authority is expressed within this permission to be "in consultation with Transport for London" (where said conditions relate to transportation matters or where they relate to transport policies in the Mayor's London Plan) then Transport for London shall be provided with schemes or details submitted upon submission and the London Borough of Ealing will take account of any comments or representations from Transport for London prior to issuing any approvals pursuant to said conditions, but if the London Borough of Ealing has provided TfL with all relevant information and documentation and has not received any response from TfL after 3 weeks, then it shall be entitled to issue any decision without needing to wait further for any response.
'Development Units' - units of development with approximately the same traffic generation
characteristics.  One Development Unit is equivalent to the following: Cl) 1 residential dwelling, or (2) 100 sqm of retail, leisure, hotel and commercial floor space.
| The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.
Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

| The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved plans A725-E02-AX-GL-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-XX-JTP-A-DR-0002 P8; A725-E02-AX-B1-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-00-JTP-A-DR-0001 P7; A725-E02-AX-01-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-02-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-03-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-04-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-05-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-06-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-07-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-08-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-09-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-RF-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-ELE-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-ELE-JTP-A-DR-0002; A725-E02-AX-ELE-JTP-A-DR-0003; A725-E02-AX-ELE-JTP-A-DR-0004; A725-E02-AX-ELE-JTP-A-DR-0005; A725-E02-AX-SEC-JTP-A-DR-0001; A725-E02-AX-SEC-JTP-A-DR-0002; A725-E02-AX-SEC-JTP-A-DR-0003 and A725-E02-AX-SEC-JTP-A-DR-0004 as prepared by JTP architects;

A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0001 REV B; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0002; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR0003; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR0004; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0005; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0006; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0007; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0008; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0009; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0010; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR0012; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0013; A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-DR-0014 and A725-E01-A0-HED-LS-SPC-0001 as prepared by HED Landscape Architects; Phase A Design and Access Statement dated February 2016 as prepared by JTP architects; Phase A Wind Study dated 10 February 2016 reference RWDI  1600034-DS Revision C as prepared by RWDI Consulting Engineers & Scientists; Daylight & Sunlight Report dated 10 February 2016 reference AJ-MC-ROL7163 as prepared by Anstey Horne; Phase A Transport Statement Revision 4.0 dated 12 February 2016 as prepared by Atkins.
Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning.

| Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved prior to the commencement of development of this Phase 'A' of development further details of refuse collection points, secure cycle parking storage, car parking space layout within the basement areas as they relate to safety zones, junction design and perpendicular bays shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority, Ealing Council.  Such details shall thereafter be implemented in accordance with those approved details and be thereby retained.

Reason: To secure an inclusive, safe and high quality built environment for all users of the site and be sustainable, and where appropriate constrain local highway impact.  In accordance with policies 6.9, 6.13, 7.2 and 7.3 of the London Plan 2015; Policies 1.1(e), 1.1(f), 1.1(g) and 1.1(h) of Ealing's adopted Development (or Core) Strategy 2026 (2012); Policies 6.13 and 7.3 of Ealing's Development Management DPD, 2013.

|  The details of hard and soft landscaping including the tree protection and tree planting proposals as submitted to and hereby approved by the local planning authority shall be laid out and planted prior to the occupation of this phase of development.  Any trees or shrubs which within 5 years of planting, die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased shall be replaced with the same species of the same size or an approved alternative to the satisfaction of the local planning authority during the next planting season.  The landscaping shall be retained thereafter.
Reason: To ensure that the development is landscaped in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies 7.19 and 7.21 of the London Plan 2015.

| Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved, details for the installation of Ultra Low NOx communal gas boilers with maximum NOx emissions of under 0.040 g/kWh.  shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the Commencement of Development of this Phase 'A' of development.  The works, as approved, shall be completed prior to occupation of this Phase of development and thereafter be retained.

Reason: To minimise the impact of building emissions on local air quality in the interests of health, in accordance with policies 3.2 and 7.14 of the London Plan 2015; the Mayor's Sustainable Design and Construction SPG; policies 1.1(e) and (j) of Ealing's Development (or Core) Strategy 2012, and policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD.

| Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved, details of the green roofs and SuDS system of this Phase (Phase A) of development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the Commencement of Development of this Phase 'A' of development.  The development shall thereafter be carried out in accordance with the approved plans and details.

Reason: In order that the Local Planning Authority could be satisfied with the design of the amenity areas and public realm, and to ensure that the resulting development is provided with an acceptable scheme of private, semi-private and public amenity space and enhances the biodiversity value of the site, in accordance with the policy requirements set out at paragraph 74 of the NPPF and policies 7.19 and 7.21 of the London Plan 2015;  1.1(e), 1.1(i), 1.2(d), 5.4 and 5.5 of Ealing's Development (or Core) Strategy 2012; and policy 7D of Ealing's Development Management DPD.
